delegates.description:
The validation delegate. With the help of this delegate you can validate value of some object easily.

```js
framework.onValidation = function(name, value) {
    switch (name) {
        case 'firstname':
            // You can return Boolean
            return value.length > 0;
        case 'lastname':
            // You can return a string (it's meant as error message)
            return Utils.parseInt(value) === 0 ? 'Age is not valid' : true;
    }
};
```

properties.description:
Returns framework custom functions. You can define your own functions into it.

```javascript
framework.functions.toUpperCase = function(value) {
    return value.toString().toUpperCase();
};
```

__Usage__:

```javascript
console.log(framework.functions.toUpperCase('peter'));
console.log(FUNCTION('toUpperCase')('peter'));
```

A global property for storing values.

__Example__:

```javascript
framework.global.MAX = 10;

// Get the value
console.log(framework.global.MAX);
console.log(controller.global.MAX);
```

View:

```html
<div>Max: @{global.MAX}</div>
```

This property stores helper functions for view engine.

__Example__:

```javascript
framework.helpers.sum = function(a, b) {
    return a + b;
};
```

View:

```html
<div>@{sum(10, 10)} === 20</div>
```

api.description:
The main class (core) of total.js. This class is singleton and is set as global variable.

```javascript
require('total.js');

console.log(framework.version);
// is same as
console.log(F.version);

F.on('load', function() {
    console.log('Framework is loaded.');
});

// Run the framework
F.http(‘debug’);
```

methods.description:
Creates a `image resize` route.

__Example__:

```javascript
framework.resize('/img/medium/*.jpg', 200, 200, { grayscale: true, rotate: 40 }, '/img/');
framework.resize('/img/large/', 600, 400, null, '/img/', ['.jpg', '.png']);
framework.resize('/img/large/', 600, 400, { blur: true, grayscale: true, sepia: 80, flop: true, flip: true, rotate: 30, quality: 80 });
```

Creates a new file route. This function can handle static files.

__Example__:

```js
framework.file(‘*.jpg’, function(req, res, isValidation) {
    if (isValidation)
        return req.url.lastIndexOf(‘.jpg’) !== -1;
    // ... transform
    res.file('new-file-name.jpg');
});
```

Appends a new error. If this method does not contain any arguments then returns a function.

__Example: framework.error() as delegate__:

```js
db.update({}, framework.error());

// Is same as:
/*
db.update({}, function(err) {
   if (err)
      framework.error(err);
});
*/
```

Writes the image/picture into the response. A file extension must exist in `config['static-accepts']`. This function sets up HTTP cache (according to the framework config mode - `debug` or `release`) and the processed image is saved into the temporary directory.

__Examples__:

```javascript
framework.responseImage(req, res, stream, function(image) {
    image.resize('50%');
    image.output('png');
    image.minify();
});
```

Writes the image/picture without cache, slowly than `responseImage()`. A file extension must exist in `config['static-accepts']`.

__Examples__:

```javascript
framework.responseImageWithoutCache(req, res, stream, function(image) {
    image.resize('50%');
    image.output('png');
    image.minify();
});
```

Checks if `ETag` or `Last Modified` header is modified.

```javascript
    if (compare === String)
        console.log('The framework compares ETag with the compare value.');
    else if (compare === Date)
        console.log('The framework compares Date with the compare date.');
```

If framework doesn't find a difference then responds 304 (not modified). If the content is modified then function returns `true`.

api.description:
