```javascript
framework.cache.add('key', 'value', ‘5 minutes’);
console.log(framework.get(‘key'));

// OR (is the same as)

controller.cache.add('key', { name: 'Peter Širka' }, new Date().add('minute', 10));
console.log(controller.get(‘key'));
```

methods.description:
Returns a function for classic node.js callback(err, some_data).

Example:

framework.database('some_db').all(controller.callback());

// or

framework.database('some_db').all(controller.callback('my-view'))

api.description:
Is created when a request is received into the WebSocket controller.

__Example__:

```javascript
controller.on('open', function(client) {
    console.log('FrameworkWebSocketClient -->', client);
};

controller.on('close', function(client) {
    console.log('FrameworkWebSocketClient -->', client);
};

controller.on('message', function(client, message) {
    console.log('FrameworkWebSocketClient -->', client);
};
```

